  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston describes the activities of Maria and Henry Chapman, including an account of their illnesses. She also decribes her own illness. She mentions the Morgan School in a discussion of family plans. Caroline writes: &quot;The Britannia brought a box of things val[ued] $300 from Glasgow and a beautiful piece for Liberty Bell from Richard Webb.&quot; The American &amp; Foreign Anti-Slavery Reporter has ceased publication.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Written cross-wise on page 1, there is a short note by Anne Warren Weston to Deborah Weston. Anne gives family news.</subfield>
